.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-SIFT 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-sift \- remove already-present changes from a batch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch sift
\fB\-\-from\fR \fISOURCE_BATCH\fR
\fB\-\-to\fR \fIDEST_BATCH\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sift
compares a batch with the current working tree state, removes portions whose
effect is already present, and writes the remaining unapplied portion to the
destination batch.
.PP
If
.I DEST_BATCH
equals
.IR SOURCE_BATCH ,
the batch is updated in place. Otherwise the destination batch must not already
exist, and the source batch is preserved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-from " SOURCE_BATCH
Read changes from
.IR SOURCE_BATCH .
.TP
.BI "\-\-to " DEST_BATCH
Write remaining changes to
.IR DEST_BATCH .
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
git-stage-batch sift --from feature --to feature-pruned
git-stage-batch sift --from feature --to feature
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-reset (1)
